<h1 id="main">Community</h1>
<p>
Most important part of any Open Source project is an active community.<br />
On this page you'll find ways to get into touch with other Phrozn users and contributors. 
</p>

<h2 id="irc-channel">IRC Channel</h2>
<p>
If you have any questions or suggestions, both on using and extending Phrozn,
join us at <b>#phrozn</b> channel on <a href="http://freenode.net">freenode.net</a>.

Generally, IRC channel is your best bet when you seek quick answer/solution.
</p>

<h2 id="issue-tracker">Issue Tracker</h2>
<p>
To report problem, or suggest feature, please, use <a href="https://github.com/farazdagi/phrozn/issues">issue tracker on github</a>.
</p>

<h2 id="twitter">Twitter Account</h2>
<p>Project account: <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/phroznproject">@PhroznProject</a></p>
<p>You can always contact me via by personal twitter account as well: <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/farazdagi">@farazdagi</a>. </p>

<h2 id="how-to-contribute">Contribute to Phrozn</h2>
<p>
Contributing to Phrozn is very easy - just <a href="https://github.com/farazdagi/phrozn">fork the project</a> on github, work on your copy and file pull requests.<br />
If you need assistance on comprehending Phrozn internals, just send me a message using twitter or IRC.
</p>
